ProtoDefines:
. "Let $n\in\mathbf{N}$ and $x\in\mathbf{Z}$ and suppose that 
   $\gcd(x,n)=1$. The order of $x$ modulo $n$ is the smallest 
   $m\in\mathbf{N}$ such that $$ x^m \equiv 1\pmod{n}. $$"
